<subSubSection id="7268FB898390706110D7B00193FBBB61" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="35C2D5ED1B0FC046E21396AC10C19BE0" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="43F95D13942E363BC6E73503404A1EAC" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicName id="8552AF21D5E960EBA2E5486FB4BB0DB1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia cubana" order="Myrtales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cubana">
<emphasis id="4AE690CFD047B7516A14B4DD357B3957" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Miconia cubana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="1765B984321D34D7EB9884E5D2D50145" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia asperifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asperifolia">
<emphasis id="DFC11960C2572A86352EFA0DE5FC40BA" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Miconia asperifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considering the large, expanded, cymose inflorescences and the reduced bulla-based hairs (not filling the areoles) that are seen in some specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="A870F9C53AA6B3CB7C0DE7D53F39F6DE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia asperifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asperifolia">
<emphasis id="4414D9F9F3CB5BC356C62F68907600A7" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Miconia asperifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
